President Trump visited the U.S.-Mexico border in Calexico, California and made remarks about immigration and border security. He discussed the progress being made on building a border wall and the impact it has had on reducing illegal immigration. The president also highlighted the need for immigration reform and criticized the current asylum system. He praised the efforts of Border Patrol agents and other law enforcement officials in securing the border. The president also thanked Mexico for their recent efforts in apprehending and returning migrants. Various officials, including Border Patrol agents, law enforcement representatives, and California Assemblywoman Melissa Melendez, spoke about the challenges they face and the importance of border security.